  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "When the controller-attach-detach refactor was done, code was added to the Kubelet to annotate the node in a way that the attach-detach controller recognizes as meaning that the controller should manage attach/detach for attachable PVs scheduled to that node.  However, this is only done **if the node does not already exist**.  If the node already exists, the API registration code will only delete and recreate it if the `ExternalID` field has changed.  The correct behavior is for the annotation for controller attach-detach to be set based on the current configuration of the Kubelet, whether the node already exists or not.\n\nI am working on a fix for this now -- will submit a PR tomorrow, probably, but wanted to record the bug.\n\ncc @kubernetes/sig-storage \n",
